    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "exactly. and if there's no inherent value, then any decision we make is just a choice between two equally neutral states. if life is just momentum and death is just the absence of momentum, then choosing to stop isn't \"bad\" or \"wrong\"—it's just a neutral logical pivot. isn't it more rational to just accept that the void is just as valid an option as staying?",
